The paper discusses a novel learning algorithm for data stream mining, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The algorithm is designed to cope with rapidly changing environments, which is a common issue in neural networks (cs.NE) and control systems (cs.SY). The paper also addresses the problem of data uncertainty, which is relevant to data management (cs.DM). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG and cs.AI, followed by cs.NE, cs.SY, and cs.DM.
